P(X = 2) = \frac{1}{6} \cdot \frac{\binom{2}{2}}{\binom{6}{2}}
P(X = 1) = \frac{1}{6}\cdot P(X = 1 | \mbox{6 thrown}) + \frac{5}{6} \cdot P(X = 1| \mbox{1,2,3,4 or 5 thrown})
P(X = 1 | \mbox{6 thrown}) = \frac{\binom{2}{1}\binom{4}{1}}{\binom{6}{2}}
P(X = 1 | \mbox{1,2,3,4 or 5 thrown}) = \frac{2}{6}
P(X = 0) = 1 - P(X=2) - P(X= 1)
